Package org.hms.entities

Class AbstractTable<T extends AbstractTableEntry>

java.lang.Object
org.hms.entities.AbstractTable<T>
Type Parameters:
T - the type of entries in the table, extending AbstractTableEntry
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
ContactInformationTable, DrugInventoryTable, DrugReplenishRequestTable, MedicalRecord, PatientTable, StaffTable
public abstract class AbstractTable<T extends AbstractTableEntry> extends Object implements Serializable
An abstract class representing a table that maintains a collection of entries. Each entry is an instance of a class that extends AbstractTableEntry. This class provides methods to add, remove, replace, and search for entries, as well as to save the entries to a CSV file.

    • filterByAttribute

      public <U> AbstractTable<T> filterByAttribute(Function<T,U> keyExtractor, U keyValue)

      Filters the table entries by a specified attribute using a key extractor function. Returns a new table containing only entries where the extracted key matches the provided value.

      Adding or deleting the entries in the result table will not affect the original table. However, mutating the entries in the result table WILL MUTATE THE ENTRIES IN THE ORIGINAL TABLE.

      Type Parameters:
      U - the type of the key used for searching
      Parameters:
      keyExtractor - a function that extracts the search key from an entry
      keyValue - the value to match against
      Returns:
      a new table containing only entries where the extracted key matches the keyValue
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if keyExtractor or keyValue is null
      RuntimeException - if an error occurs while creating the new table

    • filterByCondition

      Filters the table entries by a specified condition using a key extractor function and a predicate. Returns a new table containing only entries where the condition is met.
      Type Parameters:
      U - the type of the key used for filtering
      Parameters:
      keyExtractor - a function that extracts the key from an entry

      predValue - the value to match against using the predicate

      a new table containing only entries where the condition is met
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if keyExtractor, pred, or predValue is null
      RuntimeException - if an error occurs while creating the new table

    • filterByCondition

      public <U> AbstractTable<T> filterByCondition(Function<T,U> keyExtractor, Predicate<U> pred)
      Filters the table entries based on a condition specified by a key extractor function and a predicate. Returns a new table containing only entries where the condition is met.

      This method can be used if you want to chain conditions to filter by.

      Type Parameters:
      U - the type of the key used for filtering
      Parameters:
      keyExtractor - a function that extracts the key from an entry
      pred - the predicate to test the extracted key
      Returns:
      a new table containing only entries where the condition is met
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if keyExtractor or pred is null
      RuntimeException - if an error occurs while adding an entry to the result table

    • filterByCondition

      public <U, V> AbstractTable<T> filterByCondition(Function<T,U> keyExtractorA, Function<T,V> keyExtractorB, BiPredicate<U,V> pred)
      Filters the table entries based on conditions specified by two key extractor functions and a predicate. Returns a new table containing only entries that satisfy the condition.

      This method can be used if you want to chain conditions to filter by.

      Type Parameters:
      U - the type of the key extracted by the first key extractor
      V - the type of the key extracted by the second key extractor
      Parameters:
      keyExtractorA - a function that extracts the first key from an entry
      keyExtractorB - a function that extracts the second key from an entry
      pred - the predicate to test the extracted keys
      Returns:
      a new table containing only entries where the condition is met
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if keyExtractorA, keyExtractorB, or pred is null
      RuntimeException - if an error occurs while adding an entry to the result table

    • loadFromFile

      public void loadFromFile(String filename) throws IOException
      Loads entries from a CSV file, specified by the given filename. The file is expected to have a header line, which will be skipped. Each subsequent line is treated as a CSV representation of an entry.
      Parameters:
      filename - the path of the file from which to load the entries
      Throws:
      IOException - if an I/O error occurs during the file reading

    • loadFromFile

      public void loadFromFile() throws IOException
      Loads entries from a CSV file specified by the `filePath` and populates the `entries` list. It clears any existing entries before loading new ones. The method reads each line of the file, skipping the header line, and converts each line into an entry using `createValidEntryTemplate()` and `loadFromCSVString(String)`.
      Throws:
      IOException - if an I/O error occurs while reading the file.

    • getUnusedID

      public int getUnusedID()
      This method retrieves the first unused ID in a list of entries that have a sequential order of IDs. It sorts the entries by their ID and then iterates through the list to find the first gap in the sequence.
      Returns:
      the first unused ID in the sequence starting from 0. If all IDs from 0 to the size of the list are used, it returns the size of the list.
